: 1758040901:0;## Intro
: 1758040902:0;The overall unit is called Stasis. The Stasis Consists of the:
: 1758040902:0;In the case of OFAF (one fill all fill), the system(s) accomodate for master/slaves.
: 1758040902:0;KonaGUI - can be used to set up master/slave status.
: 1758040902:0;Liquid Nitrogen Plumbing assembly - has mechanical connections for daisy chaining slaves to the Liquid Nitrogen source tank.
: 1758040902:0;DeviceHardware - has two ethernet ports to accomodate daisy chaining additional slave units.
: 1758040902:0;## Freezer
: 1758040902:0;Actual Stainless Steel unit that houses liquid nitrogen and samples.
: 1758040902:0;## Liquid Nitrogen Plumbing
: 1758040902:0;The liquid nitrogen plumbing is an assembly that consists of various hardware and sensors with the goal of faciliating liquid nitrogen transfer into the freezer unit.
: 1758040902:0;The plumbing accomodates for daisy chaining additional plumbing assemblies.
: 1758040903:0;### Solenoids
: 1758040904:0;The unit contains 2 Solenoids in series that open up to allow the transfer of Liquid Nitrogen from a tank to the freezer. The second solenoid is a backup in case the first one is in a stuck state. The Device hardware has means to check on states of the solenoids and whether they're stuck.\
\
There is another solenoid that is used as a pressure relief valve when pressure builds up in the system during filling.\
